    "description": "The strategy implements the January Barometer effect on US equities by using January performance of the S and P 500 proxy to select a full risk-on or risk-off allocation for the remainder of the year. It targets the behavioral and macro information embedded in early-year equity returns, hypothesizing that a positive January indicates favorable risk appetite and forward growth expectations, while a negative January signals elevated downside risk where capital preservation is preferable.\n\nThe investable universe is limited to two daily priced ETFs: SPY (US large-cap equities) and BIL (1 to 3 month US Treasury bills as a cash substitute). The strategy records the SPY price at the start of January, then at the start of February computes SPY total price return over January; if the return is positive it holds 100 percent SPY, otherwise it holds 100 percent BIL. Portfolio decisions occur on a scheduled monthly cadence and positions are set via full notional targeting with no leverage, no volatility scaling, and no explicit stop-loss or drawdown control beyond the binary shift into T-bills. A one-year warm-up is used to ensure the January reference price is available before live allocation.",
